common --enable_bzlmod
test --test_output=errors --test_summary=terse
# Memory bounding is Τ·mem: each pk_calc declares a resource_set (the learned mem.json bucket via
# the bib generator's ladder), and Bazel's local scheduler bounds concurrent sweeps against
# --local_ram_resources (default HOST_RAM*.67) — no rc pool needed.  The old --local_extra_resources
# mem_mb pool (the membudget→tags projection) was never wired and is retired.
# Τ·mem·observe — isolate each action in its own cgroup so it can read its OWN tree-peak memory
# (/sys/fs/cgroup/<action>/memory.peak — the only tree-accurate channel; Bazel's log has no peak,
# and systemd-run is dead in the scrubbed sandbox env).  OPT-IN (needs cgroup-v2 + the new cgroup
# impl), so default builds stay portable on non-cgroup machines; run `bazel build … --config=memobserve`
# to populate the learned-mem manifest, which then refines the portable reservations for everyone.
build:memobserve --incompatible_use_new_cgroup_implementation --experimental_sandbox_memory_limit_mb=HOST_RAM
# Τ·mem·observe·clean — turn the peak read ON only here; default builds write a clean 0 (the read OFF
# would be the SHARED-cgroup garbage), and the flag is part of the calc action key (observe-vs-default
# cache as distinct actions, so no stale measured/0 peak crosses configs).
build:memobserve --//tools:observe=True

# Ζ·mutant·eval — the def-sweep's counterfactuals run as NORMAL actions in the HERMETIC linux-sandbox
# (hardlinks + chroot), so a check's Path(__file__).resolve() and its subprocesses CANNOT follow
# symlinks out to the source tree — they see only the staged inputs (the mutated engine at its
# canonical path).  The system dirs are mount-paired for bash/python+libs; the SOURCE tree is NOT
# mounted, so it stays unreachable.  Standard-FHS dirs → portable across Linux.
build:mutant --experimental_use_hermetic_linux_sandbox
build:mutant --sandbox_add_mount_pair=/bin --sandbox_add_mount_pair=/usr
build:mutant --sandbox_add_mount_pair=/lib --sandbox_add_mount_pair=/lib64 --sandbox_add_mount_pair=/etc
